PRESIDENT DONALD Trump has accused China of being a currency manipulator, after the Chinese currency “po qi” or “cracked 7” against the US dollar— a psychologically significant value—for the first time in over a decade. How will this escalation of the US-China trade war affect global markets? Also, how useful are yield curves for predicting future recessions? And, life without Uber. Rachana Shanbhogue presents. Runtime: 20 min    Listen on: Apple Podcasts | Spotify | Google | Stitcher | TuneIn